Weather Girl Version 1.4.2

Credits:

Overlay effects: Reverend/Bubblobill
Sounds and some minor tinkering: Wolph42

notes:
The sounds will work out fo the box as they are linked to my dropbox, however I would suggest to create your own links and replace these in the sound macros.

Version 1.0
- first release with version number
- added sounds. 
- made leaf table images smaller

Version 1.1
- added Parade overlay

Version 1.2
- fixed some overlay names
- moved Environment Lighting back to its own macro

Version 1.3
- moved macroLink execution to UDF "runMacro"
- split up into separate overlays mostly based on input groupings
	* fx.Ambience (sfx)
	* fx.Lighting (Environment lighting)
	* fx.Lightning(will change one day to something more generic)
	* fx.Space	  (Space)
	* fx.Surround (Border)
	* fx.Weather  (Actual weather)
- fixed some typos and fiddly bits

Version 1.3.1
- stores previous selection and prepopulates input fields

Version 1.3.2
- updated input to handle more layers

Version 1.3.3b
- replaced launcher with Frame form
- added argument receiving code to each overlay

Version 1.3.3b1
- reformatted frame launcher
- tidying up
- added more controls for some overlays
- bug fixes
- added "setStartStopMacros" which sets the macro commands for "Set FX" and "Stop FX" so that they launch with this token's name.
- updated notes

Version 1.3.3b2
- notes updated with sound instructions
- sounds added to launcher

Version 1.3.3b3
- added Bubbles Overhead
- added radial gradient type to Gradient Edge

Version 1.3.4
- added underwater sound
- cleaned up sound buttons

Version 1.3.5
- reworked launcher layout

Version 1.3.6
- added "Bloodied" and "Splat" overlays
- added more controls for "Falling Leaves", "Birds", and "Swarm"

Version 1.4
- changed z-order to be more intuitive
- added player names argument to runMacro
- improved "Splat" to dispose of token
- added ability to play multiple sounds
- launcher layout accordioned for overlay and sound selection
- added sound controls for volume, loop, start position, stop position
- moved preferences for devcache, number of overlays, and number sounds to lib property
- moved sound links to lib property
- fixed stopLocal to accept 0 arguments to stop all sounds

Version 1.4.1
- fixed "Splat"
- added VFX & SFX Shortcuts panels
- updated notes
